I've made this several times now and it is always a hit. Tonight I made it using a small pork loin instead of chops. Seared off the loin and finished it in the oven at 375. I typically use about half of the recommended onion and at least double the apples. It also usually takes longer than the noted 5 minutes to thicken the sauce (more like 8-10, at least). I sliced up the pork loin, topped with the apple mixture and served with israeli couscous with cranberries and a side of broccoli. Definitely something I will make again and again. Even my 2.5 year old will eat it!

