Rating: 0
delicious. modified the recipe slightly - used almost double the ingredients in the apple curry in order to make more, almost triple the apples (2.5 large granny smiths), and double the marjoram and thyme. seared the chops and then baked in a covered pan for 20 minutes at 425. sauteed onions until soft and tan, then added apples and garlic and continued to saute until soft - not mushy. set aside and added curry ingredients, cooked until nice and thick, then added apples/onions/garlic back in to rewarm. added a tsp. of cinnamon at the end. I also used phukit green curry powder, a slightly fruity, moderately hot curry powder, which complemented the apples nicely. The chops were extremely juicy and well seasoned and we are already dreaming of other uses for this incredible curry.

