Rating: 4
Excellent combination of flavors. With my improvements, I would give it 4 forks! I increased the herbs to 1 1/2 tsp each. Method also needs improvement. I browned the chops quickly on both sides and finished them by placing them in a oven-proof saute pan and roasted them in the oven for about 20 minutes at 375-400 degrees while I made the sauce. For the sauce I sauteed the onions in the drippings first till they softened and developed color, then added the garlic, sauteeing gently till softened, then added the apples (I used tart, baking style apples that would retain their shape). Cooked the apples till they began to soften. Removed the apple mixture and set aside. Deglazed the pan with the wine, stirred in the broth, cooked until reduced by half. Then stirred in the cream, mustard, curry powder, herbs, fresh ground salt & pepper to taste. Boiled until slightly thickened. Stirred in apple mixture to briefly re-warm. Then serve.

